13/07/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivica Racan arrived in Sarajevo on Sunday (13 July). In remarks to the Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) news agency FENA, Racan expressed optimism about resolving issues still open between the two countries, including refugee returns and co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal. Racan added that Croatia would support and assist BiH in the process of Euro-Atlantic integration. Accompanying Racan are Foreign Minister Tonino Picula, Transport Minister Roland Zuvanic and Reconstruction Minister Radimir Cacic. (FENA, HINA, BBC, NTV Hayat - 12/07/03)
